	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="96" facs="EHRI-ET-SOV003_96.jpg"/>
			<p>The things we know is far from everything there is…</p>

			<p>Told by <persName ref="#ehri_et_dogon_r_h">R.H. Dogon</persName></p>

			<p>in: The Blood Cries for Vengeance!: What Victims tell about the <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans"
					>Fascist</term> Atrocities in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-632" type="subject"
					>Occupied</term>
				<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>, collected and assembled by <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_kvitko_leyb">L. Kvitko</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_nusinov_yitskhok">Y. Nusinov</persName>, and <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_katsnelson">Y. Katsnelson</persName>; Forword: <persName ref="#ehri_et_epshteyn_shakhne">Shakhne Epshteyn</persName>
					(<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/524901/moscow.html">Moscow</placeName>: Der Emes, <date when="1941">1941</date>),
				96–99</p>

			<p>On the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-750" type="subject">Jewish cemetery</term> of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">Przemyśl</placeName>, there is a fresh <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-539" type="subject">mass grave</term>. This is the most horrific document
				of the savage bestiality of our times.</p>
			<p>In the white stone, small tablets are attached on which the names of all those are engraved who were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">murdered</term> in a horrific way during the 14 days
				of <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-632" type="subject">occupation</term> in <date when="1939-09">September
					1939</date>.</p>
			<p>Who knows, how many would have been added to their number, if the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076"
					type="subject">Red Army</term> had not pulled out this bloody piece of land from <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans"
					>Hitlerites’</term> paws.</p>
			<p>Ten little tables on the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-539" type="subject">mass grave</term> are
				entirely empty, – no name is engraved on them. They were people who did not have any documents on them, and their <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">bodies</term> were so crumbled up that one could not
				establish who they were.</p>
			<p>In those terrible days, the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo men</orgName> drove around
				the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">city</placeName> like bloodthirsty rascals. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">They snapped up people they coincidentally bumped
					into, arranged them in rows</term>, gave the order <q>hands on the neck</q> and let them stand like this for several hours. At the
				same time, other <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo-men</orgName> entered different houses
				and dragged out people from them, – very often it was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292"
					type="subject">sick</term> people dragged from their beds.</p>
			<p>They loaded the people group by group on trucks and drove them out of the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">city</placeName>, ostensibly to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">No one of them came back alive</term>, however. There,
				they were arranged in rows of five. They ordered the first five <pb n="97" facs="EHRI-ET-SOV003_97.jpg"/> to dig up graves for
				themselves, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">shot at them with dumdum bullets, pulled
					out their eyes alive, cut off limbs, cut out tongues</term>. The survivors of the last row had to hastily <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-746" type="subject">bury</term> the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">dead</term> and prepare graves for themselves again
				until everyone was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">dead</term>. This way, a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">father</term> had to witness the early <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term> of his <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">son</term>; a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> had to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-746" type="subject">bury</term> his <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> with his hands before he himself <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">perished</term> from the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">murderous hands</term>.</p>
			<p>Only from one <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> with the name of
					<persName ref="#ehri_et_soyfer">Soyfer</persName>, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerites</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">killed</term> a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">father</term>, a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">son</term>, and a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">son-in-law</term> simultaneously. The dry goods
				merchant <persName ref="#ehri_et_zaltsberg">Zaltsberg</persName>, a calm, quiet, and in the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">city</placeName> well-respected <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">man</term>, was found with his hands around the throat
				of his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">19-year old son</term>. This <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">son</term>, a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1214" type="subject">student</term>, had a reputation as a very talented
				mathematician, and not only his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">parents</term>
				prided themselves with him; his professors predicted a career of a scientist. I myself saw how one of his teachers, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainian</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_makhnatski">Makhnatski</persName>, brought flowers to his grave on his yortsayt<note place="bottom"
					>anniversary of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term>.</note>.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_grosman">Grosman</persName>, a quiet, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292"
					type="subject">sick</term> person, who did nothing else in his life than studying books, was dragged out from his <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sickbed</term>. Ignoring the pleas and laments of his
				old, disabled <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term>, who is not able to move
				and for whom the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">son</term> was her only support, he
				was taken away and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">killed</term>.</p>
			<p>The <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> summoned the 70-year old <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_rozenboym_nekhemye">Nekhemye Rozenboym</persName> and informed <persName ref="#ehri_et_rozenboym_nekhemye"
					>him</persName> that he has to take care of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-746" type="subject"
					>burial</term> of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">murdered</term> and at the
				very end a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">bullet awaits him as well</term>.</p>
			<p>They made <persName ref="#ehri_et_rozenboym_nekhemye">Rozenboym</persName> and several other Jews stand with their faces turned to the
				wall and ordered them to say vide <note place="bottom">confession of sin said collectively on Yom Kippur and individually before
					dying.</note>, because they would be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">shot</term>
				in 15 minutes. While the Jews said vide, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject"
					>murderers</term> prepared their rifles, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">whilst
					making fun</term> of their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-132" type="subject">victims</term>, and
				made all necessary preparations for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject"
					>execution</term>. Suddenly, they were summoned from someone and the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo men</orgName> left behind those sentenced to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term>. The Jews did not dare to move from the
				spot convinced that this is something of a new trick of the bloodhounds. When no one came back after some time, they left <pb n="98"
					facs="EHRI-ET-SOV003_98.jpg"/> and to this day they cannot say whether the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> intentionally plotted this <q>game</q> or whether
				they simply forgot about them because a new <q>game</q> came up.</p>
			<p>A <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term> (I forgot her name) went to the
					<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName>, – she wanted to plead for the release of
				her <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term> from their hands. So they
				suggested to her that she should bring ransom in the amount of four thousand Złoty. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term>, who never in her life possessed such a
				sum of money, decided to do the impossible in order to save her <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822"
					type="subject">husband</term>. She sold everything from her home, remained with one <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">shirt</term> and one <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">dress</term>, but it did not suffice. So people pooled
				however much one could afford and we gathered the necessary sum of money.</p>
			<p>On the second day, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term> came to the
					<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> with money. They <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">took the money from her</term> and ordered her to come
				back tomorrow. Then they will release her <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject"
					>husband</term>.</p>
			<p>The next day, they ordered her to wait a little in the corridor. Suddenly, she heard from above her coming from the first floor a
				mocking laughter: <q>Here you have your <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject"
						>husband</term>.</q> Then, at the same time, she saw something dark rolling down the stairs.</p>
			<p>The horribly mutilated <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">dead body</term> of her <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term> rolled towards her feet.</p>
			<p>It became clear that at the point that they conducted the negotiations regarding the ransom with the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term>, her <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">husband</term> had already not been alive anymore.</p>
			<p>In those days, in the city of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">Przemyśl</placeName> alone 580 people were
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">killed</term>. Only a part of them have been
				able to be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-746" type="subject">buried</term> so far – 168, because the
					<term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Nazis</term> did not <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536"
					type="subject">kill</term> their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-132" type="subject">victims</term>
				in one place but dragged them into woods and to fields and deserted mountains. Those, who were found, were found thanks to the
				peasants who after the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> had left pointed to the locations from where wild
				clamor and shootings were heard. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Women</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mothers</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">daughters</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">fathers</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">sons</term> walking around the fields, teared open the
				freshly closed soil and searched for traces of their relatives. Finding mutilated <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">bodies</term> with teared-out eyes, cut-out tongues
				and cut-off limbs, it was difficult, however, to recognize the former individuals.</p>
			<p><pb n="99" facs="EHRI-ET-SOV003_99.jpg"/> In the small shtetl <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/772772/dynow.html"
					>Dynów</placeName>, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerites</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject">massacred</term> approximately 400 people, among
				them very many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-304" type="subject">refugees</term> – from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Western Poland</placeName>.</p>
			<p>In the shtetl <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3091788/milicz.html">Milicz</placeName>, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerites</term> chased 70 Jews into the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3091788/milicz.html">beys-medresh</placeName>, among them many <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">old men</term>, locked them in and set the building on
				fire from all sides. Everyone <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-646" type="subject">burnt</term> to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term> alive. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-682" type="subject">Jewish writer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_keytlman_y">Y. Keytlman</persName>’s <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822"
					type="subject">sister</term>, a young <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject"
					>girl</term> who did not live far, got so upset from this calamity that she went insane. She was in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/702550/lviv.html">Lviv</placeName> in a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-282" type="subject">mental hospital</term>.</p>
			<p>In the city <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">Przemyśl</placeName>, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerites</term> set the old <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogue</term> from the 15th century on <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-646" type="subject">fire</term>, which was of great artistic value. When
				the firemen started to extinguish the fire, <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Nazis</term> came running and cut open the
				rubber hose with knives.</p>
			<p>In the city of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770380/jaroslaw.html">Jarosław</placeName>, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerite</term> general was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">killed</term>. Since no traces of the one behind it
				could be found, all <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1214" type="subject">students</term> of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134" type="subject">gymnasium</term> were gathered, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">boys</term> in the ages from 12 to 18, and every tenth
				of them was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">shot to death</term>.</p>
			<p>We know little about the things that are happening right now in these territories because the people who managed to save themselves,
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> on the eve the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerite</term> invasion.</p>
			<p>I spoke to a Jew from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">Przemyśl</placeName>, the butcher <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_broyn">Broyn</persName>, who was with the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> for 24 hours
				before the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">Red Army</term> took back the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">city</placeName>. Immediately after the entry into the <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">city</placeName>, on Sunday, <date when="1939-06-22">June 22</date>, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerites</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">shot</term> everyone who appeared on the streets.
				Many <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainians</term> and <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Poles</term> died
				who went out to welcome them convinced that the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerites</term> would receive them
				well.</p>
			<p>From <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7530748/przemysl.html">Slovatskega Street No. 7</placeName>, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerites</term> dragged out all residents and chased them to the other side of the river
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/759610/san.html">San</placeName>. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">son</term> of the Nayshteter <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735" type="subject">rabbi</term> tried to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term>. They caught him and got ready to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">shoot</term> him in front of everyone’s eyes. An
				elderly <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">lady</term> with the name of <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_zirber">Zirber</persName> threw herself to their feet and begged them to give him life. They <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">shot</term> both <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">dead</term>.</p>
